# Refresh app after Flutter changes

When you edit `lib/` or other app code in this project:

1. Run `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File tools/refresh_app.ps1` from the project root.
2. Prefer the connected Android phone (SM S721B). Wait until the script reports the app is on the phone.
3. Briefly tell the user to check their phone screen.

Do this at the end of every implementation turn that changes the running app, unless the user says otherwise.
